§MATHE — mechanism summary (no recycled metaphors beyond standard CS citations)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  - Lamport (1978): logical ordering without trusting wall clocks.
  - Fidge; Mattern (1988): vector clocks refine concurrent vs ordered events.
  - `is_causally_ready`: (1) sender component must be exactly predecessor+1;
    (2) for every other peer P in the **incoming** vector, local[P] >= V[P].

  Library code uses **no print()**; failures return structured reasons via
  `check_readiness(...) -> (bool, str|None)`.

